  "read": "TileLang two-kernel sparse-MLA backward pipeline gate. The first kernel consumes real q/dO/output/lse plus compressed KV and packed group ids, recomputes P and scaled dP, and writes packed BF16 slabs as [2, S, topk, H]. The second kernel immediately feeds those slabs into the selected-limit MFMA final-dKV consumer and returns usable [groups, D] dKV. This is a concrete test of whether adjacent TileLang producer/consumer staging can beat the current sparse-atomic wall before implementing true on-chip segmented reduction. This run feeds real TorchTitan sparse-MLA boundary tensors into the TileLang dKV producer. Materialized per-head probs and scaled grad_logits are present only for materialized-input modes or correctness-reference checks; recompute mode uses q/dO/output/lse/compressed KV in the timed producer. This run also launches a correctness-preserving TileLang spill kernel for actual-LI panel overflow pairs. The packed panel path uses original selected-slot weights, and the spill path adds the dropped original LI pairs back into final dKV.",
